verbs.description: strobilate (third-person singular simple present strobilates, present participle strobilating, simple past and past participle strobilated)

entries.meaning: (intransitive, biology) To produce a strobilus (layered, conelike structure).
examples: These, in turn, reproduce by cloning; when conditions are right, they ‘strobilate’, elongating and splitting into a stack of discs which develop into larvae, and break away to become medusae.
